'''Émile Beaussire''' (26 May 1824, [[Luçon]] - 28 May 1889) was a French [[Republicanism|republican]] politician and a philosopher. He was a member of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]] from 1871 to 1876 and of the [[Chamber of Deputies (France)|Chamber of Deputies]] from 1876 to 1877 and from 1879 to 1881. He belonged to the ''Centre gauche'' parliamentary group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.assemblee-nationale.fr/sycomore/fiche.asp?num_dept=543 |title=Base de données historique des anciens députés - Assemblée nationale |publisher=Assemblee-nationale.fr |date= |accessdate=2013-05-07}}</ref>
